#1 Resected rectal adenocarcinoma with positive lymph nodes
#2 Resected metastatic liver disease
Basic cancer education has been provided to the patient at the request of Dr. Guillory and Dr. Jessie Brackett.  I have had the opportunity to review the operative report, surgical pathology, laboratory values, and notes in Documents Browser.  I have reviewed these findings with the patient and answered questions.  I have discussed this case in detail with Dr. Mckinney, my collaborating physician, who has guided my plan.
We have discussed the characteristics of the cancer, including the type of malignancy, size, grade, lymph node status, and stage of the cancer.
Mr. Thomas is interested in returning to the Alcorn Home for formal treatment evaluation.  Therefore, I have made follow-up arrangements for the patient to return in approximately four weeks to be evaluated by Dr. Brown.  I will coordinate an appointment with Dr. Gillespie to discuss the feasibility of resection of his pulmonary lesion.  He understands that at some point he will probably be eligible for further chemotherapy, but the ultimate plan will be decided at a later date.  At that time, he will undergo a CT-scan of the chest, abdomen, and pelvis, comprehensive lab panel, and a postoperative evaluation with Dr. Powell.  Mr. Thomas and his family verbalized understanding and wish to proceed.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

